Edward B. Cloues IIChairman Of Amrep , Palm Coast Data LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships69--
Background

		Mr. Edward B. Cloues, II, also known as Ed, served as a Secretary of Virtua, Inc. Mr. Cloues served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer of Penn Virginia Corporation from October 26, 2015 to September 12, 2016. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at K-Tron International Inc. from January 5, 1998 to April 1, 2010. Prior to joining K-Tron International Inc. in 1998, Mr. Cloues was a Partner in the law firm of Morgan, Lewis & Bockius LLP from October ... 1979 to January 1998 and was also its Senior Partner, where he specialized in mergers and acquisitions and general business law counseling. He serves as the Chairman of AMREP Corporation at Palm Coast Data LLC. He has been Chairman of Penn Virginia Corporation since July 2011. He served as Chairman of Penn Virginia Resource GP LLC, the General Partner of Penn Virginia Resource Partners LP from July 2011 to March 2014. Mr. Cloues has been a Director of AmeriQuest Technologies Inc. since December 1998 and AMREP Corporation since 1994. He has been a Director of Hillenbrand, Inc. since April 2, 2010. He serves as a Director of Chamber of Commerce of Southern New Jersey and Penn Virginia Resource Partners LP, ESOP. Mr. Cloues serves on the Boards of several other public and private companies. He served as a Director of Penn Virginia Corporation from 2001 to September 12, 2016. He served as a Director of Penn Virginia Resource GP LLC, the General Partner of Penn Virginia Resource Partners LP since January 2003. He served as a Director at K-Tron International Inc. since July 1985 until April 1, 2010. He serves as Vice Chairman of Virtua, Inc. He serves on the board of trustees of Virtua Health, Inc., a non-profit hospital and health care system and as a member of the advisory board of the Rohrer College of Business at Rowan University. Mr. Cloues has a BA from Harvard College and a JD from New York University School Of Law, where he was a Root-Tilden Scholar.Read Full Background




